jei.silentgear.blueprint.desc: Blueprints and templates are used to craft tool heads and armor. Blueprints can be reused infinitely, templates are single-use. When used in the crafting station, you can mix materials. Otherwise, the materials must all be the same. Check the tooltip of the blueprint/template for details on crafting the final item.
jei.silentgear.dagger.desc: Basically a very light sword. Low damage and shorter reach, but very high attack speed. It also reduces the target's invulnerability time when hit.
jei.silentgear.fishing_rod.desc: It's a fishing rod. What more do you want?
jei.silentgear.hammer.desc: Mines stone and ores in a 3x3 area. Ores are only broken when aiming at ores, by default.
jei.silentgear.katana.desc: A sword that is slightly faster, but a little weaker than classic swords. Katana can also reach a little further than standard swords.
jei.silentgear.machete.desc: A multi-function blade. It's a sword, axe, and sickle, but works best as a sword. Slightly slower attack speed, but higher damage than standard swords. Like sickles, it can clear an area of plants, but the range is smaller.
jei.silentgear.mattock.desc: The ultimate farming tool, capable of tilling and digging soil and chopping wood. A bit slower than a shovel or axe, but more durable. Should work in anything that requires a hoe.
jei.silentgear.paxel.desc: An all-in-one tool that functions as a pickaxe, axe, and shovel. It has a small durability bonus, but a small penalty to harvest speed and enchantability.
jei.silentgear.prospector_hammer.desc: Right-clicking a block will search a small area in that direction for blocks of interest (mostly ores). Also works like a pickaxe for mining, and can be used in some recipes like a hammer.
jei.silentgear.red_card_upgrade.desc: Tools and armor with the red card upgrade can break like their vanilla counterparts, instead of becoming a "broken" item that can still be repaired.
jei.silentgear.saw.desc: Chops down entire trees by breaking a single block. The logs and leaves must be correctly tagged to be recognized as a tree.
jei.silentgear.spoon_upgrade.desc: Let's your pickaxe mine dirt and such. Because reasons.
jei.silentgear.sword.desc: A classic sword with balanced damage and speed. The guard takes the appearance of the second material used in crafting.
jei.silentgear.tip_upgrade.desc: Allows an existing tool/weapon to be further upgraded. Most tip upgrades will add (or subtract) a fixed amount to certain stats, but some add will multipliers instead. Hold the Ctrl key to view stat modifiers in the tooltip.
jei.silentgear.tool_head.desc: Tool heads, blades, bow limbs, and more! These are the core of tools and weapons, constructed with a blueprint/template and some number of main tool materials. Check the blueprint/template tooltip for more info.
jei.silentgear.tooltip.sample2: Gear made with any materials will work

trait.silentgear.accelerate.desc: Gains harvest speed, attack speed, and ranged speed as damaged
trait.silentgear.adamant.desc: Armor increases damage resistance, tools deal more damage to mobs with a base health of more than 10 hearts
trait.silentgear.ancient.desc: Increases XP dropped by blocks and mobs
trait.silentgear.aquatic.desc: Full set of armor gives water breathing, deals more damage to aquatic mobs
trait.silentgear.bending.desc: Gear sometimes takes extra damage (cancels with Flexible)
trait.silentgear.bounce.desc: Boots negate fall damage, armor knocks back attackers
trait.silentgear.brittle.desc: Gear sometimes takes extra damage (cancels with Malleable)
trait.silentgear.chilled.desc: Deals more damage to Nether and fire-immune mobs
trait.silentgear.chipping.desc: Reduces armor or increases harvest speed as gear is damaged
trait.silentgear.crackler.desc: Creates and places basalt at the cost of durability
trait.silentgear.crushing.desc: Increases armor or decreases attack damage as gear is damaged
trait.silentgear.eroded.desc: Increases harvest speed and reduces attack damage as gear is damaged
trait.silentgear.fiery.desc: Adds Fire Aspect or Flame to appropriate gear
trait.silentgear.fireproof.desc: Cannot be destroyed when dropped in fire or lava
trait.silentgear.flame_ward.desc: Gives fire resistance on armor (full set only)
trait.silentgear.flammable.desc: Takes damage when on fire and can be used as fuel
trait.silentgear.flexible.desc: Gear occasionally takes less damage (cancels with Brittle)
trait.silentgear.floatstoner.desc: Creates and places end stone at the cost of durability
trait.silentgear.gold_digger.desc: Sometimes increases nugget drops when mining
trait.silentgear.greedy.desc: Increases the mining speed for ores
trait.silentgear.hard.desc: Increases harvest speed or decreases ranged damage as item is damaged (cancels with Soft)
trait.silentgear.holy.desc: Deals extra damage to the undead
trait.silentgear.ignite.desc: Lights blocks on fire at a small durability cost
trait.silentgear.imperial.desc: Sometimes increases gem drops when mining
trait.silentgear.jabberwocky.desc: ’Twas brillig, and the slithy toves / Did gyre and gimble in the wabe
trait.silentgear.jagged.desc: Increases attack damage or decreased ranged damage as item is damaged
trait.silentgear.kitty_vision.desc: Gives night vision on helmets and curios
trait.silentgear.lucky.desc: Adds luck when held (this is not Fortune)
trait.silentgear.lucky.desc.long: Luck is a vanilla attribute which influences loot in some cases, usually just loot chests. This has nothing to do with the Fortune enchantment! Lucky will not increase drops from ores!
trait.silentgear.lustrous.desc: Tools gain a large harvest speed boost when in light
trait.silentgear.malleable.desc: Gear sometimes takes less damage (cancels with Brittle)
trait.silentgear.mighty.desc: Gives strength and/or haste on tools based on trait level
trait.silentgear.organic.desc: Gains enchantability, but loses magic damage as the item is damaged
trait.silentgear.racker.desc: Places netherrack at the cost of durability
trait.silentgear.renew.desc: Slowly repairs the item over time
trait.silentgear.road_maker.desc: Turns dirt-like blocks into grass paths
trait.silentgear.rustic.desc: Increases synergy if it's 100% or less
trait.silentgear.sharp.desc: Gain harvest speed and attack damage as durability is lost
trait.silentgear.silky.desc: Adds Silk Touch to harvest tools
trait.silentgear.snow_walker.desc: Walk on powder snow without sinking
trait.silentgear.soft.desc: Reduces harvest speed as tool is damaged (cancels with Hard)
trait.silentgear.stellar.desc: Armor gives speed and jump boost, items slowly repair themselves
trait.silentgear.synergistic.desc: Gear gets a synergy bonus (if base value is more than 100%)
trait.silentgear.terminus.desc: Creates and places stone blocks when used
trait.silentgear.void_ward.desc: Saves the wearer from falling out of the world
trait.silentgear.vulcan.desc: Places obsidian at a high durability cost
trait.silentgear.widen.desc: Increases the effect radius of hammers and excavators
